Adult.description: American Woodcocks have shorter legs than Wilson's Snipes. They have an unmarked cinnamon belly while Wilson's Snipes have barred flanks and a white belly.

Juvenile.description: Long-billed Dowitchers have longer legs than Wilson's Snipes. They do not have long streaks down their back like Wilson's Snipes.

Nonbreeding.description: Long-billed Dowitchers have longer legs than Wilson's Snipes and are often found foraging on mudflats away from vegetation while snipes forage more often in wetlands with low vegetation.

Breeding adult (hendersoni).description: Short-billed Dowitchers have longer legs than Wilson's Snipes and are more often found foraging in open water areas unlike Wilson's Snipes, which forage in wetlands with low vegetation.

Nonbreeding adult.description: Short-billed Dowitchers have longer legs than Wilson's Snipes. They do not have long streaks down their back like Wilson's Snipes.
